summary: If they don’t care about nutrition but they’re into history, start with

colonial herb garden and teach colonial times, the kids will find plenty to eat while they’re out there.  Cafeteria staff or food service (May not be necessary for sustaining the garden, but will have to be on the team if food and nutrition education or garden-to-table are priorities.  Local Farmers (Again, they may not be necessary to sustaining an instructional garden, but if improved cafeteria food is part of your vision, farm to school is in your future.).  Attention to the soil is the most important point of starting
garden, unless you are purchasing perfect soil for raised beds.  Depending on how many children will be working at
time, you’ll need multiple rakes, shovels, trowels, clippers, scissors, hose, forks for turning soil and compost,
mallet for pounding in stakes, wire clipper, measuring tape, thermometers for air and compost).

summary: Click OK Go to workspace tree, right click on newly created workspace.  Browse Target Perforce workspace location, and click Finish Repeat the same for all projects.  Page Object Model is

design pattern to create Object Repository for web UI elements.  This Page class will find the Web Elements of that web page and also contains Page methods which perform operations on those Web Elements.  Create separate packages for separate module i.e. Community test case should be in “com.opentext.auto.cs.gui.tests.modules.cop.communities” Test case Packages should be inside CSTests 2016 and page packages should be inside CSPageFactory2016.
